Vice President Kamala Harris spoke at a meeting with Tribal leaders, emphasizing the importance of their work in upholding America's highest ideals. She highlighted the need to address disparities in education, healthcare, infrastructure, and economic opportunities that persist in Native communities due to historical injustices. Harris mentioned several initiatives the administration has undertaken, including efforts to improve maternal health in Native communities and expand access to capital for Native businesses. She also discussed the administration's commitment to climate and environmental justice, recognizing the expertise and stewardship of Native peoples. Harris expressed support for the Indian Child Welfare Act and vowed to work with Native leaders to protect its provisions. She concluded by emphasizing the administration's reliance on the friendship, leadership, and partnership of Tribal communities in building a better future for all.